docs.abstract: The internet giant is being sued by former employees who say the company is going too far with diversity. Other lawsuits accuse it of the opposite.
docs.snippet: The internet giant is being sued by former employees who say the company is going too far with diversity. Other lawsuits accuse it of the opposite.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In 2014, Google became one of the first technology companies to release a race and gender breakdown of its work force. It revealed — to no one’s surprise — that its staff was largely white or Asian and decidedly male.

headline.main: Google Is Trying Too Hard (or Not Hard Enough) to Diversify
headline.print_headline: Diversity Rifts Inside Google Bring Clash Of Lawsuits

docs.abstract: It can be tempting to hook up everything you love to the internet. But take a moment to appreciate some of the objects that can remain unplugged.
docs.snippet: It can be tempting to hook up everything you love to the internet. But take a moment to appreciate some of the objects that can remain unplugged.
docs.lead_paragraph: It still feels magical to light up your living room by saying “Alexa, turn on the lights.” But with all the hype surrounding so-called smart things — everyday devices that are connected to the internet — it’s easy to forget that sometimes the dumb stuff is just better.

headline.main: In an Era of ‘Smart’ Things, Sometimes Dumb Stuff Is Better
headline.print_headline: In ‘Smart’ Things Era, Sometimes Dumb Is Better

docs.abstract: To fight layoffs and other cost-cutting, a group of 13 held signs and chanted outside Alden Global Capital, a hedge fund that owns more than 90 publications.
docs.snippet: To fight layoffs and other cost-cutting, a group of 13 held signs and chanted outside Alden Global Capital, a hedge fund that owns more than 90 publications.
docs.lead_paragraph: Noelle Phillips, a reporter for The Denver Post, was among the journalists who took part in a protest against the newspaper’s hedge-fund owner in Midtown Manhattan on Tuesday. Along with a dozen other sign-wielding protesters from newspapers across the country, Ms. Phillips chanted slogans outside the Lipstick Building, where Alden Global Capital, the company behind the newspaper chain Digital First Media, has its headquarters.

headline.main: Denver Post Journalists Go to New York to Protest Their Owner
headline.print_headline: New York Crowd Rips Denver Post’s Owners
